    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "If the state is provided from somewhere else (like the URL or any cold storage like the local-storage) we would still need to have a way to provide a plain JS Object. In the case of this proposal we can still instanciate a new SearchParameters with just the JS object but this makes the implementation less straightforward.\r\n\r\n```js\r\nvar coldState = getStateFromSomewhere();\r\nvar h = algoliasearchHelper(client, index, () => new SearchParameters(coldState));\r\n```",
